The body of a 40-year-old man was found at the foot of a 20 metre cliff at Nondabula in Ndwedwe, KwaZulu-Natal on Friday. According to paramedics, a passer-by discovered the body and reported the incident to the police. Police search and rescue, metro police and IPPS medical rescue services made their way to the scene. According to IPSS spokesperson Paul Herbst, when they arrived, it appeared the body had started to decompose - a sign that it had been there for quite some time.  The cause of the man's death is still unclear at this point.  https://www.news24.com/news24/southafrica/news/mans-decomposing-body-found-at-the-foot-of-kzn-cliff-20200626 